OL,6,FAhead of reading the poem, Ms Martin
OL,7,Ftold the inquiry how she and Ms
OL,8,FGibson, who were both engaged, planned
OL,9,Fthe sequencing of their weddings.
OL,11,F"Esther had suggested, she had said
OL,12,Fbecause I was the younger sister to
OL,13,Flet me have my date first," she said.
OL,15,FMs Martin then read out the poem,
OL,16,Fwhich described her older sister as a
OL,17,F"silent special bridesmaid" and
OL,18,Frecounted how a bouquet of flowers
OL,19,Ftied with a blue ribbon was left on a
OL,20,Ftable in the church to symbolise her.
