OL,6,FThe final line of the poem read:
OL,7,F"Broken spirits, shattered dreams,
OL,8,Fblue ribbons holding together
OL,9,Fmemories, sweet memories that will
OL,10,Flinger always."
OL,12,FAfter it was read to the inquiry, Lord
OL,13,FTurnbull thanked the family for
OL,14,Fsharing their memories of Ms Gibson.
OL,16,F"Esther was plainly a caring and
OL,17,Fgenerous Christian person with a
OL,18,Fstrong sense of community, whose life
OL,19,Fand personality acted as a good role
OL,20,Fmodel for others," he said.
