OL,6,F"Like a number of those killed on that
OL,7,Fday, Esther was on the brink of a new
OL,8,Flife full of promise and happiness,
OL,9,Fwhich she was so cruelly robbed of.
OL,11,F"Her absence will have constituted a
OL,12,Fprofound loss to her family and to all
OL,13,Fwho shared her company."
